2 Introduction

Demonstration MSE projections were undertaken for the preliminary Green Sea Urchin operating model of Statistical Area 14. Here we project the current exploitation rate (curE) and the current catches (CurC) and evaluate projection outcomes with respect to yield, variability in yield and limit and target biological reference points


3 Performance Evaluation

3.1 MP Framework metrics

Preliminary performance metrics are presented that correspond with those detailed in Anderson et als (DFO 2021) groundfish MP framework:

  1. LT LRP: Probability B > 0.4BMSY (over long-term year range)
  2. LT USR: Probability B > 0.8BMSY (over long-term year range)
  3. FMSY: Probability F < FMSY (over entire projection)
  4. STC: Probability catch > reference catch (over years 110)
  5. LTC: Probability catch > reference catch (over long-term year range)
  6. AADC: Probability AADC (average absolute interannual difference in catch) < historical AADC (over entire projection)


Figure 1. Trade-off plot showing probabilities associated with all 6 metrics described above from DFO (2021). Shaded areas show straw-dog rejection areas: LT_LRP < 0.8, P(F<FMSY) < 0.8, LT_USR < 0.6, P(AADC > 0.1) < 0.5, STC < 0.5, LTC < 0.5. Those MPs that meet all requirements (fall in the white region in all plots) are satisficed.
